The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Dhoni to join team later
                                                                                                                       7                                      Dhoni to join team later
                      
	Chennai: The Indian cricket team will leave for Sri Lanka from here Friday to play three Tests and a tri-series, also featuring New Zealand, from July 18. Captain Mahendra Singh Dhoni will join the side later.         
	The pace duo of Sreesanth and Abhimanyu Mithun, who replaces the injured Zaheer Khan, arrived in the city.         
	Sachin Tendulkar missed his morning flight and is expected to arrive here in in the evening, said an airport official. Other players are also expected to arrive here late Thursday or early Friday.         
	Dhoni, who got married recently and arrived here in the evening, will be joining the side later. The Team India captain is scheduled to be present at a function organised by the Madras Cricket Club on Friday evening. (PTI)                                                                                                                     
